## Step 0: Classify the Question

Before doing anything else, classify the question into one of these types. This determines your strategy:

| Type | Indicators | Strategy |
|------|-----------|----------|
| **Single value lookup** | "What is X as of date Y?" | grep → read → extract → answer |
| **Multi-year time series** | "For years 2010-2024...", "across 12 years" | bash loop → Python array → compute |
| **Calculation** | "geometric mean", "CAGR", "volatility", "Euclidean norm", "HP filter", "Theil index" | extract data → Python script |
| **Date/text answer** | "On what date...", "Which country..." | grep → read → extract text/date |
| **Comparison** | "difference between", "ratio of" | extract both values → compute |
| **Visual/chart question** | "chart", "plot", "exhibit", "local maxima" | search for underlying tabular data → compute |
| **Counting** | "How many times", "count the number" | extract series → Python count |

