## Page-Reference Questions

The corpus files do NOT have page markers. To handle questions that reference specific pages:
1. The **Table of Contents** (near the top of each bulletin file) maps section names to page numbers
2. Use the ToC to find which section is on the target page
3. Then grep for that section's content in the file
4. For "pdf page X" vs "report page Y" — the ToC uses report page numbers

